n\nTo implement this, we need to do the following:\nDFSInputStream\n1. move DFSInputStream out of DFSClient\n2. add member variable to keep track of current datanode (the chosen node)\n\nDistributedFileSystem\n1. change reportChecksumFailure parameter crc from int to FSInputStream (needed to be able to delete it). \n2. determine specific block and datanode from DFSInputStream passed to reportChecksumFailure  \n3. call namenode to delete block/crc vis DFSClient\n\nClientProtocol\n1. add method to ask namenode to delete certain blocks on specifc datanode.\n\nNamenode\n1. add ability to delete certain blocks on specific datanode","customfield_10010":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_12312026":null,"customfield_12312023":null,"customfield_12310320":null,"customfield_12312024":null,"customfield_12312340":null,"attachment":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/attachment/12348609","id":"12348609","filename":"hadoop-855-5.patch","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-10T01:55:05.303+0000","size":17187,"mimeType":"text/plain","content":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12348609/hadoop-855-5.patch"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/attachment/12348878","id":"12348878","filename":"hadoop-855-7.patch","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-13T00:05:08.341+0000","size":17845,"mimeType":"text/plain","content":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12348878/hadoop-855-7.patch"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/attachment/12349048","id":"12349048","filename":"hadoop-855-9.patch","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-16T22:41:10.210+0000","size":18020,"mimeType":"text/plain","content":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12349048/hadoop-855-9.patch"}],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"customfield_12312341":null,"customfield_12312220":null,"customfield_12312022":null,"customfield_12310921":null,"customfield_12310920":"106718","customfield_12312823":null,"summary":"HDFS should repair corrupted files","creator":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"subtasks":[],"customfield_12310291":null,"reporter":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"customfield_12310290":null,"aggregateprogress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"customfield_12311024":null,"environment":null,"customfield_12313520":null,"customfield_12311020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12462257","id":"12462257","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Mostly this sounds good to me.\n\n> 1. change reportChecksumFailure parameter crc from int to FSInputStream\n\nI'm confused by this one.  There's already an FSInputStream parameter.  In the DistributedFileSystem implementation of this method, one can cast this to DFSInputStream and then access whatever implementation-specific state is needed (like the datanode where the block in question resides).  So I see no need to alter the reportChecksumFailure signature.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2007-01-04T17:11:38.321+0000","updated":"2007-01-04T17:11:38.321+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12462301","id":"12462301","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"What I meant by that change is to pass in two FSInputStreams (and range information).  We have an FSInputStream for the data file, but we also need one for the checksum file to be able to delete the corrupted block from the checksum.   \n\nIn my first pass, when the checksum doesn't match, both the data and checksum blocks will be deleted.  Should we also try to figure out which of the two was corrupt?   Will the extra effort be worth the gain in not rewriting a block that was not actually corrupt?\n\n  \n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-04T19:41:28.077+0000","updated":"2007-01-04T19:41:28.077+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12462306","id":"12462306","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"> we also need one for the checksum file\n\nAh, I get it.  That sounds reasonable.  Thanks for clarifying!\n\n> Should we also try to figure out which of the two was corrupt?\n\nI don't think it's worth it, at least not for the first pass.\n\nWhat should we do if the replication level is one for the corrupt block?  Keep it, I think.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2007-01-04T20:07:36.390+0000","updated":"2007-01-04T20:07:36.390+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12462310","id":"12462310","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"If the replication level is one, then we will keep the corrupt block and report the error.   ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-04T20:19:25.390+0000","updated":"2007-01-04T20:19:25.390+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12462350","id":"12462350","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"DFSInputStream also needs a method to return the current block. We could either have a memember variable to keep track of the current block or calculate the block based the member variables pos and blocks.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-04T22:47:22.691+0000","updated":"2007-01-04T22:47:22.691+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12463446","id":"12463446","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"I've added a member variable to keep track of the current block.  ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-10T01:54:40.102+0000","updated":"2007-01-10T01:54:40.102+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12463635","id":"12463635","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"We should probably call the protocol method something like invalidateBlock() rather than deleteBlock(), since it only deletes it if has replicas.\n\nAlso, does this issue include HADOOP-731 or not?  If so, then it needs more work.  If not, we should re-open HADOOP-731.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cutting","name":"cutting","key":"cutting","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Doug Cutting","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2007-01-10T17:11:43.422+0000","updated":"2007-01-10T17:11:43.422+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12463645","id":"12463645","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sameerp","name":"sameerp","key":"sameerp","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34061","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34061","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34061","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34061"},"displayName":"Sameer Paranjpye","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"This patch does not include HADOOP-731, I've re-opened it.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sameerp","name":"sameerp","key":"sameerp","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34061","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34061","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34061","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34061"},"displayName":"Sameer Paranjpye","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2007-01-10T17:55:39.458+0000","updated":"2007-01-10T17:55:39.458+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12463737","id":"12463737","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"1. src/java/org/apache/hadoop/dfs/NameNode.java\n     In deleteBlocks, I would not enforce one location per block.\n2. src/java/org/apache/hadoop/dfs/FSNamesystem.java\n     In deleteBlocks, should we make sure that the remaining containing datanodes contain at least one non-decomissoned/ing datanode when deciding if a block should be deleted? We need to check if the block is underreplicated before putting it to needReplications. Also need to check if the block should be taken out of excessReplicationMap.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=hairong","name":"hairong","key":"hairong","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Hairong Kuang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2007-01-10T22:40:40.464+0000","updated":"2007-01-10T22:40:40.464+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12359755/comment/12463770","id":"12463770","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wchien","name":"wchien","key":"wchien","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Wendy Chien","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Thanks Doug and Hairong for looking over the patch. \n\na. I'll change the name from deleteBlocks to invalidateBlocks\nb. I'll take away the one location enforcement in NameNode\nc. I'm going to call removeStoredBlock to update the data structures in invalidateBlock.  We need to do everything it does.  (It updates blocksMap, neededReplications, and excessReplicateMap)\nd. I agree with Hairong that we should not delete the corrupt copy if it is the only one on a live node, in case the decommissioned nodes are taken down.  I will implement it this way unless people disagree. ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https:/